This is Holi season and Nanha, the little boy, is really exited. He has discovered some characters, which if mixed in some proportion, can give a beautiful color. 
Nanha already has some characters, that can form colors. He then goes to a shop of colors and checks out the list of colors the shopkeeper has. He wants to know the colors in the list, that contains all the characters that he has.
To help out Nanha, his bestie, Yaar Kumar (a.k.a Lemon Kumar) comes to rescue.

Input

First line contains an integers T, the number of test cases. Then T test cases follow.
Each test case has three lines of input.
First line contains an integer n the number of colors in the list.
The next line contains n number of strings, depicting each color.
Then it contains the characters, that Nanha has.


Output
For each case, print the colors from the list that contains all the characters that Nanha has.
 Note

The order of the list must be followed, while printing the output.
If no colors from the list has all the characters, that Nanha has, then print a blank line.


Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 10
1 ≤ n ≤ 1000
1 ≤ Length of colors ≤ 1000
1 ≤ No. of characters that Nanha has ≤ 1000
